table.name: genotype_region
table.remarks: polymorphic regions from a genotype, delineated by markers in a certain linkage group on a certain map

column.name: phenome_genotype_id
column.remarks: optional genotype this region belongs to. some regions are artificial, arising from combinations of other regions, and thus do not have an associated genotype

column.name: marker_id_nn
column.remarks: the north marker in the pair of markers bracketing the north end of this region. this may be null for regions at the north end of a linkage group

column.name: marker_id_ns
column.remarks: the south marker in the pair of markers bracketing the north end of this region

column.name: marker_id_sn
column.remarks: the north marker in the pair of markers bracketing the south end of this region

column.name: marker_id_ss
column.remarks: the south marker in the pair of markers bracketing the south end of this region. this may be null for regions at the south end of a linkage group.

column.name: lg_id
column.remarks: the linkage group in a specific version of a specific map where this region is located

column.name: type
column.remarks: the type of polymorphic region this is. map is mapping experiment data, inbred is IL lines segments, and bin is a derived region based on a boolean combination of inbred fragments. For bin regions, the specific boolean combination of fragments that make the bin is not stored.

column.name: name
column.remarks: special name for this region, if any. optional

column.name: sp_person_id
column.remarks: the person who loaded this datum. optional
